Canada’s Chretien, Martin to Join Ignatieff's Liberal Campaign, Globe Says

-- B y   S e a n   B .   P a s t e r n a k
-- 
2011-04-16T13:48:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-16/canada-s-chretien-martin-to-join-ignatieff-s-liberal-campaign-globe-says.html
Jean Chretien and Paul Martin,
former Canadian prime ministers, will join the national election
campaign tour of Liberal Party leader  Michael Ignatieff , the
Globe and Mail reported on its  website , without saying where it
got the information.  Martin, the country’s leader from 2003 to 2006, will
address a rally planned in Edmonton,  Alberta , tonight, the
newspaper said. Chretien, prime minister from 1993 to 2003, is
scheduled to appear at an event Toronto in the week before the
May 2 federal election.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sean B. Pasternak in Toronto at 
 spasternak@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
